Date: Sat, 18 Jul 2026 12:18:06 -0500
Subject: [PATCH 09/13] mb87030: drop the redundant second scsi_disconnect on
 bus-free

When the initiator is connected and the bus goes fully free, the
bus-free monitor at the top of step() calls scsi_disconnect() (which
moves the SPC to Idle), then the switch below re-enters case
State::Idle and, if PCTL_BUS_FREE_IE is set, calls scsi_disconnect()
again in the same step(). It is idempotent (scsi_disconnect() assigns
INTS_DISCONNECTED and parks in Idle), so this is not a functional
fault, but the second call is pointless. Return right after the monitor
fires so the Idle case doesn't repeat it.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
Claude-Session: https://claude.ai/code/session_01LK3cToPNL8r9RQCFCS3uUB
---
 src/devices/machine/mb87030.cpp | 3 +++
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+)

diff --git a/src/devices/machine/mb87030.cpp b/src/devices/machine/mb87030.cpp
index c9f755c926a..adc9fdd9ec7 100644
--- a/src/devices/machine/mb87030.cpp
+++ b/src/devices/machine/mb87030.cpp
@@ -318,6 +318,9 @@ void mb87030_device::step(bool timeout)
 		LOG("SCSI disconnect\n");
 		scsi_disconnect();
 		scsi_set_ctrl(0, S_ALL);
+		// scsi_disconnect() already moved the SPC to Idle; return so the switch below does not
+		// re-enter the State::Idle bus-free path and issue a second, redundant scsi_disconnect().
+		return;
 	}
 
 	switch (m_state) {
